HEADWORD: Historionomer
<hw>His*to`ri*on"o*mer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
history + <?/ to distribute.]</ety> <def>One versed in the phenomena of
history and the laws controlling them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>historionomers</qex> will have measured accurately the
sidereal years of races.</q> <rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

